13/11/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and his Macedonian counterpart, Branko Crvenkovski, met on Wednesday (12 November) and agreed on joint measures against organised crime and human trafficking. 
In all, three agreements envisioning enhanced co-operation were signed. 
Nastase and Crvenkovski also discussed issues related to their countries' bids for EU and NATO membership. 
Crvenkovski reiterated that Macedonia would apply for official EU candidate status within months. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 13/11/03; MIA, Rompres, BBC - 12/11/03)
